A social commentator and chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Femi Fani-Kayode, has mocked Vice President, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo over his current predicament at the Presidential Villa. Report emerged yesterday that over 30 presidential aides attached to the Vice President were disengaged by President Buhari without his (Osinbajo) knowledge. DAILY POST reported that Fani-Kayode, a former Minister of Aviation, had previously listed ten ways President Muhammadu Buhari has undermined the VP. In a mockery post he shared on Twitter on Thursday afternoon, Fani-Kayode said, “After wetting his bed, short man devil shed tears and said ‘how could my father do this to me? “‘I betrayed my people, my faith, my zone, my region, my pol. mentor and everyone else just for him! I even gave him my soul! Yet he can still do this to me? Dolapo pl. bring me panadol!'”(sic). Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.